NamecoinToBind 1.0
==================

This version supports the original and first spec :
- '{"map": {"": {"ns": ["10.0.0.1"]}}}'
- '{"map": {"": "62.16.239.10"}}'

Install idn (php5-idn crash with some domain names, so the idn binary is used) :
  apt-get install idn

Edit the file namescan.php to point to a running namecoin (on line 7) :
  $namecoin = new jsonRPCClient('http://user:pass@127.0.0.1:8336/');

Edit the file /etc/bind/named.conf.options and add :
  // zones generated by the users
  include "/etc/bind/namecoin/bit-forward.conf";
  include "/etc/bind/namecoin/bit-domains.conf";

Create the following folders :
- /etc/bind/namecoin/
- ./cache
- ./q

Launch : ./update_domains_bind.sh &

